Prepared my first little solo showing of work for display @daydreamsurfshop ☀️ while shooting a surf retreat in Baja 🌵 🌊. I landed on seven images from the past few years that I love individually but also felt cohesive to the overall look and feel of my body of work — capturing a range of beauty in natural light and colors, wide open spaces, and the quieter, peaceful moments on this planet 🌏. I also created a newspaper 🗞️ portfolio zine to highlight a few other favorites in a new medium. All are available for sale — and still on display @daydreamsurfshop for a little while longer 💙✨

I’m beyond excited to get this project between myself (@palette.supply) and the incredible and sweet @studiostandard_ team, out into the world today! It’s been months in the making— over 20 mock-up images and 8 incredible templates designed specifically toward the needs of photographers and brands— shot list and art direction templates, social stories, and more. The collection is live on both @studiostandard_ and @palette.supply websites. Use code SSPAL15 over on www.palette.supply for 15% off your first order! 🙃💕

I fell in love with design early in my photography career, as I got the opportunity to photograph the work of various artists and designers, from fashion to interiors. It became apparent to me how harmoniously these two practices work together and the relationship between design and photography is something I aim for as a theme in my work, from color palette to composition. So it was a dream to work closely with @studiostandard_ to develop this first collection— a collaboration of mock-ups for designers and design templates for photographers. Here’s one of my favorites— some skincare/home goods products among architectural elements. See the whole collection over @palette.supply (www.palette.supply) ✨💕

Launched a set of digital products this week over @palette.supply that include templates of my dreams! Shot list, art direction, portfolios for pitching to brands, a portfolio of selected work to present to an inquiring brand. Drag and drop templates that make all of these things we are constantly creating from scratch look way more polished and professional, and done in less than half the time 🥳 Each template has 20+ unique layouts designed by @studiostandard_  Use code SSPAL15 at www.palette.supply for 15% off your first order from the collection ✨

A couple months ago I teamed up with @studiostandard_ to create a set of templates and digital products for @palette.supply with photographers and designers in mind. I am always searching for these type of templates to help me make quick, professional and high-quality proposals, shot lists, etc. but I’ve never found ones specific to the needs of photographers, so we made them 🙃 My favorites are the Art Direction and Mood (seen here adapted as a client project proposal)— and the Shot List, an in-depth template to plan and present to your client, or for your own use as a brand. I’m super proud of these and how they can help creatives like you and I present our work better, plan our shoots better and do it in less than half the time, with professional designs. Check them all out @ www.palette.supply or @studiostandard_ ✨
